01:00:11.790 --> 01:00:14.530
on some additional
considerations,

01:00:14.530 --> 01:00:17.500
whether or not you
have a mirror symmetry.

01:00:17.500 --> 01:00:20.650
If you have a mirror symmetry,
you cannot have terms of that

01:00:20.650 --> 01:00:22.320
are odd and x.

01:00:22.320 --> 01:00:27.040
Whether or not you have some
condition on U and minus U may

01:00:27.040 --> 01:00:30.580
or may not forbid third order
terms in [? U ?] [? by  the ?]

01:00:30.580 --> 01:00:31.330
x.

01:00:31.330 --> 01:00:35.370
So once I go beyond
the quadratic level,

01:00:35.370 --> 01:00:39.500
I need to rely on some
additional symmetry statement

01:00:39.500 --> 01:00:43.750
as to which additional terms
I am allowed to write down.

01:00:43.750 --> 01:00:44.280
Yes?

01:00:44.280 --> 01:00:48.030
AUDIENCE: Also the coefficients
could depend on x, right?

01:00:48.030 --> 01:00:48.640
PROFESSOR: OK.

01:00:48.640 --> 01:00:50.550
So one of the things
that I assumed

01:00:50.550 --> 01:00:55.730
was this symmetry, which
means that every position

01:00:55.730 --> 01:00:58.940
in the crystal is the same
as any other position.

01:00:58.940 --> 01:01:02.905
So here, if I break and
make the coefficient

01:01:02.905 --> 01:01:06.800
to be different from here,
different from there,

01:01:06.800 --> 01:01:12.020
it amounts to the same thing,
that the starting point was not

01:01:12.020 --> 01:01:13.282
the crystal.

01:01:13.282 --> 01:01:14.740
AUDIENCE: Shouldn't
that be written

01:01:14.740 --> 01:01:16.906
as-- in the place where you
wrote down the symmetry,

01:01:16.906 --> 01:01:21.187
it should be U of x plus
c inside the parenthesis?

01:01:21.187 --> 01:01:21.770
PROFESSOR: No.

01:01:21.770 --> 01:01:22.790
No.

01:01:22.790 --> 01:01:24.270
So look at this.

01:01:24.270 --> 01:01:31.340
So if I take Un and I
